freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: Could have come from anywhere since Ive been out and about,  but have had runny, drippy nose since late this morning.  Feel fine but have had to blow nose frequently.  Took aspirin (since 2 weeks beyond second shot) to see if it would dry it up.

Relationship to vaccine?  Noticed difference past week. All have varied reactions to virus/shots. So could be related.  Menopause hot flashes were lessening after 20 years of them, in last week have shot up again. Maybe got triggered by second shot?

freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Going back to first evening after second shot, much pain in arm second time.  Had to put ice pack on arm overnight to ease.

I have had no symptoms today but on Saturday (2/20) I did following my 10.30am shot.  At approximately 9pm Saturday, I quite suddenly starting feeling poorly after having been fine all day.  Within a half hour after 9pm, I had to stop everything I had been doing a lay down for the night.  I felt like a ton of bricks had hit me all at once.  I aches in every muscle and bone, had headache, some chills, much fatigue, and felt flu-like all over.  Night was difficult and uncomfortable and got little sleep.  Felt much the same all day Sunday (2/21), Sunday night and into Monday morning.  By Monday noon, I seemed to be back to normal.  Have felt fine since then and today is Wednesday.   No other symptoms have surfaced since Monday.
Light diarrhea and runny nose and cough during late night/early morning hours, but all disappeared by morning.  Not sure if from second shot or because of something else.
